<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0035 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents some results of the general investigations which werecarried out within the research project 'Ascertainment of the SafetyReserves in the Transmission Chain Building - Component in Case of Earthquake'in order to clarify the influence of local non-linearities. The seismicresponse of single-degree-of-freedom-systems and two-degrees-of-freedom-systemsdue to yielding, friction and gaps is presented. The importance of theconsideration of those effects due to economic and safety demands isdemonstrated.</TEXT></DOC>